The 'ghost' of one of Australia's most notorious criminals is still lurking within the walls of his old jail cell in Melbourne - or so a group of frightened lawyers have been led to believe.

A recent group of visitors were recently tormented by what they believe to be the voice of Mark 'Chopper' Read, who died last year at the age of 53, during a ghost tour of the now desolate Pentridge Prison.

It was in this prison that the notorious Read had both his ears chopped off by a fellow inmate back in the late 1970s.

